source.name: Post- Isaac Emergency Demolitions
source.description: Buildings that experienced severe structural failure as a result of Hurricane Isaac, 8/28-8/30/12.  Many of these buildings were blighted before Isaac, but the storm exacerbated their condition to a point where they were deemed a threat to public safety, and were expedited as IDC cases, or "Imminent Danger of Collapse"
